==English==

===Etymology===
# Old English ''Scotas'', meaning Irish.  From late latin ''Scotii''.
# A member of the [[Irish]] Scots tribe who settled in Scotland in the dark age.

===Pronunciation===
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɒts|-ɒts]]

===Adjective===
'''Scots'''
# Pertaining to, or characteristic of, [[w:Scotland | Scotland]] or its people.  An alternate form of [[Scottish]] (adj.), esp. in Scotland.

===Proper noun===
{{wikipedia|Scots language}}
'''Scots'''
# A dialect of English spoken in [[w:Scotland|Scotland]], descended from Anglian and Northumbrian dialects of Old English, and today spoken primarily in the central, northeastern and southern regions of the country.

